      "title": "Longest Increasing Streak",
      "topics": [],
      "fastest": true,
      "reverse": false,
      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "#include <stdio.h>\n\nint main() {\n    int n;\n    scanf(\"%d\", &n);\n\n    long prev, curr;\n    scanf(\"%ld\", &prev);\n\n    int current = 1;\n    int best = 1;\n\n    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {\n        scanf(\"%ld\", &curr);\n        if (curr > prev) {\n            current++;\n            if (current > best) best = current;\n        } else {\n            current = 1;\n        }\n        prev = curr;\n    }\n\n    printf(\"%d\\n\", best);\n    return 0;\n}",
      "statement": "Compute the length of the longest contiguous strictly increasing subsequence in a sequence of integers.\n\nThe subsequence must be contiguous.\nThe subsequence must be strictly increasing (each element greater than the previous one).\nAt least one element is always present.",
